'''El Clásico''' ({{IPA-es|el ˈklasiko}}; {{lang-ca|El Clàssic}},<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpunt.cat/noticia/article/8-esports/48-barca/329919-el-classic-es-jugara-dilluns.html |publisher=[[El Punt]] |accessdate=18 November 2010 |date=18 November 2010 |title=El clàssic es jugarà dilluns |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231000103/http://www.elpunt.cat/noticia/article/8-esports/48-barca/329919-el-classic-es-jugara-dilluns.html |archivedate=31 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> {{IPA-ca|əl ˈklasik|pron}}; {{lang|en|"The Classic"}}) is the name given in [[association football|football]] to any match between fierce rivals [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] and [[FC Barcelona]]. Originally it referred only to those competitions held in the [[La Liga|Spanish championship]], but nowadays the term has been generalized, and tends to include every single match between the two clubs: [[UEFA Champions League]], [[Copa del Rey]], etc. Other than the [[UEFA Champions League Final]], it is considered one of the biggest club football games in the world, and is among the most viewed annual sporting events.<ref name="BBC History">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/7773758.stm|title= Barca & Real renew El Clasico rivalry|last=Stevenson|first= Johanthan|date=12 December 2008|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=15 August 2010}}</ref><ref name="Forbes 2014">[https://www.forbes.com/sites/kurtbadenhausen/2014/05/16/lionel-messi-agrees-to-new-50-million-a-year-deal-with-barcelona/ "Lionel Messi Reaches $50 Million-A-Year Deal With Barcelona"]. Forbes. Retrieved 1 October 2014</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/is-messi-vs-ronaldo-bigger-than-the-super-bowl/#fn-3|title=Is Messi vs. Ronaldo Bigger Than The Super Bowl?|author=Benjamin Morris|work=FiveThirtyEight}}</ref> A fixture known for its intensity, it has featured [[Goal celebration|memorable goal celebrations]] from both teams, often involving mocking the opposition.<ref name=“Marca”/><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eiNZ1QDb9JU El Clasico: Real Madrid Vs Barcelona • Fights, Fouls, Dives & Red Cards]</ref>

The rivalry comes about as [[Madrid]] and [[Barcelona]] are the two largest cities in Spain, and they are sometimes [[Party identification|identified]] with opposing political positions, with Real Madrid viewed as representing [[Spanish nationalism]] and Barcelona viewed as representing [[Catalan nationalism]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballblog.co.uk/castilian-oppression-v-catalan-nationalism-el-gran-classico.html |title=Castilian Oppression v Catalan Nationalism – "El Gran Classico" |publisher=Footballblog.co.uk |date=2 September 2009 |accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2017/oct/02/barcelona-in-strange-and-symbolic-eye-of-a-storm-over-catalonia|title=Barcelona in the strange and symbolic eye of a storm over Catalonia |newspaper=The Guardian|date=2 October 2017|accessdate=9 January 2018}}</ref> The rivalry is regarded as one of the biggest in world sport.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5hR9vdLtW7NiFE65gSzW-AC1kX-eg?docId=CNG.58d42948ccc56a058e6adb1e0e63535c.c1 |title=AFP: Barcelona vs Real Madrid rivalry comes to the fore |publisher=Google.com |date=14 April 2011 |accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2002/aug/28/sport.danrookwood |location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Dan | last=Rookwood |title=The bitterest rivalry in world football | date=28 August 2002}}</ref><ref>[https://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/clubs/rivalries/newsid=106848/ "El Clasico: When stars collide"]. FIFA.com. Retrieved 21 October 2014</ref> The two clubs are among the richest and most successful football clubs in the world; in 2014 ''Forbes'' ranked Barcelona and Real Madrid the world's two most valuable sports teams.<ref name="Forbes 2014"/> Both clubs have a global fanbase; they are the world's two most followed sports teams on social media.<ref name="Global support">[http://www.marca.com/en/2014/11/13/en/football/barcelona/1415913827.html "Barça, the most loved club in the world"]. Marca. Retrieved 8 May 2015</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Barcelona becomes first sports team to have 50 million Facebook fans|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/mikeozanian/2014/01/03/barcelona-becomes-first-sports-team-to-have-50-million-facebook-fans/|publisher=Forbes.com | first=Mike|last=Ozanian}}</ref>

Real Madrid leads the head to head results in competitive matches with 95 wins to Barcelona's 93, while Barcelona leads in total matches with 113 wins to Real Madrid's 99. Along with [[Athletic Bilbao]], they are the only clubs in La Liga to have never been relegated.
