{{Economic history of Chile}} The '''Real Situado''' was an annual payment of silver from the [[Viceroyalty of Peru]] to finance the Spanish army of Chile that as result of the [[Arauco War]].<ref>Lacoste, P. 2005. El vino y la nueva identidad de Chile. ''[[Revista Universum]]'', 20, 24-33.</ref> Most of the silver came from [[Potosí]] in present-day [[Bolivia]].
